# Markdown typesetting

When writing or editing Markdown (`.md`) in this project:

## Horizontal rules (`---`)

- Do **not** overuse `---`. Use them sparingly (e.g. one after the main title block at the top of a doc, or to separate a few major parts). Do not use "---" before a heading such as `##`, `###`, etc unless the file is very long. The only exception I am aware of is markdownfiles that record a full conversation with a chatbot. Then it makes sense to separate all question-answer pairs by "---".
- Prefer blank lines and heading hierarchy to structure the document instead of repeated horizontal rules.

## Bold (`**text**`)

- Do **not** overuse bold. Use it only when you need strong emphasis (e.g. one key term per paragraph, or the first occurrence of a defined term).
- **Never** use bold inside headings. Headings are already prominent; write them in plain text.
  - ❌ `## **Important section**`
  - ✅ `## Important section`

## Summary

- Few `---`; structure with headings and spacing.
- Sparing use of `**` in body text.
- No `**` in any heading (`#`, `##`, `###`, etc.).
